Write a Java program that counts login failures only when the user is NOT "admin" and the password is wrong. Use the && operator to check conditions so the fail count increases only if needed. Print the fail count each time a non-admin login fails.
    Code:
 import java.util.Scanner;
 class Admin
 {
     public static void main(String[] args)
     {
         Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
         String username="ADMIN";
         String password="A123";
         int failcount = 0;
         boolean loginTry = true;
         while (loginTry) {
             Scanner scan=new Scanner (System.in);
                     System.out.println("Name:Subasri P");
             System.out.println("Reg no:2024503025");
 
            System.out.print("Enter your username:");
             String Username = sc.next();
             System.out.print("Enter your password:");
             String Password = sc.next();
             if (!(Username.equals(username)) && !(Password.equals(password))) {
                 failcount++;
                 System.out.println("login failed (non-admin). fail count: " + failcount);
                 System.out.print("Do you want to try again? (yes/no) : ");
                 char choice = sc.next().charAt(0);
                 sc.nextLine();
                 if (choice == 'n' || choice == 'N') {
                     loginTry = false;
                     System.out.println("final failcount :" + failcount);
                 }
             }
             else
             {
                 System.out.println("Login successful! WELCOME ");
                 break;
             }
 
        }
     }
 }
Output:
Enter your username:ADMIN
Enter your password:A123
Login successful! WELCOME
